South African Stocks Advance to Six-Week High, Boosted by Mining Companies

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-04-06T11:12:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/south-african-stocks-advance-to-six-week-high-metals-gain-boosts-miners.html
South African stocks rose for a
fourth day, reaching the highest level in six weeks, as rising
metal prices boosted shares of mining companies including
 AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  and  BHP Billiton Plc. (BIL)   The benchmark FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rallied 0.5
percent to 32,801.84 at 12:55 p.m. in Johannesburg, the
strongest intraday level since Feb. 22. AngloGold, Africa’s
largest producer of the metal, headed for the highest close in a
month, jumping 2.9 percent to 340.80 rand.  BHP Billiton , the
world’s biggest mining company, rose 0.6 percent to 277.90 rand.  Gold climbed to a record for a second day as the sovereign-
debt crisis in  Europe  deepened after Moody’s Investors Service
cut  Portugal ’s credit rating. Platinum rallied for a third day,
and copper gained on expectations faster global economic growth
will boost demand for industrial metals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
